# ChartLib

A modern, smooth, and dynamic charting library for Python developers. ChartLib provides beautiful, interactive visualizations with a focus on performance and user experience.

## Features

- Smooth animations and transitions
- Modern, customizable themes
- Interactive charts with zoom, pan, and hover effects
- Support for various chart types:
  - Line charts
  - Bar charts
  - Scatter plots
  - Area charts
  - Pie charts
  - Heat maps
- Real-time data updates
- Responsive design
- Easy-to-use API

## Installation

```bash
pip install chartlib
```

## Quick Start

```python
import chartlib as cl

# Create a simple line chart
data = [1, 3, 2, 4, 3, 5]
chart = cl.LineChart(data)
chart.title = "My First Chart"
chart.show()
```

